title: Top 25 shake-up: Gators up, Georgia down, OSU still No. 1
text:
Top 25 shake-up: Gators up, Georgia down, OSU still No. 1 Published: Monday, Oct. 5, 2015 11:36 a.m. CDT By RALPH D. RUSSO AP College Football Writer 
Ohio State remained No. 1 in The Associated Press college football Top 25 and tied a poll record Sunday, despite lagging support from the voters. 
Meanwhile, No. 2 TCU and No. 3 Baylor edged forward, No. 4 Michigan State slipped and No. 5 Utah and No. 6 Clemson took big jumps. 
After four top-10 teams lost Saturday, the rankings were rattled and five teams received first-place votes. 
The Buckeyes received 38 first-place votes, their fewest this season after beginning as the first unanimous preseason No. 1. TCU has five first-place votes, Baylor received 10, Utah has seven and No. 9 Texas A&M has one. 
The Buckeyes held off Indiana 34-27 on Saturday and have now been top-ranked 101 times, matching Oklahoma for the most in the 79-year history of the media poll. 
Welcome Back 
— No. 22 Iowa is ranked for the first time since November 2010. 
— No. 24 Toledo is ranked for the first time since November 2012. 
— No. 25 Boise State is back after falling out last month. 
Buh-bye
